  "prompt": "How long can a milkshake last out of the fridge?",
  "response": "A milkshake should only be left out of the fridge for about 2 hours at room temperature. After this time, it can start to develop harmful bacteria, which could make you sick if consumed. If the temperature is above 90\u00b0F (32\u00b0C), it's best to limit that time to just 1 hour. To ensure safety and quality, it\u2019s best to refrigerate any leftover milkshake as soon as possible.",
